INTRODUCTION 



DIRECTORY STRUCTURE 

The layout of the code is as follows: 

idyom.asd: the system definition 
utils/: general-purpose utilities 
amuse/: an interface to amuse music data interface
ppm/: the ppm* and multiple-viewpoint system modelling framework 
apps/: top-level applications for users 
data/: directory used internally for storing data 

REQUIREMENTS 

SBCL              http://www.sbcl.org 
AMUSE             rvw.doc.gold.ac.uk:/isms/group/muthic/darcs/amuse/  
AMUSE-MTP         ditto 
AMUSE-VIEWPOINTS  rvw.doc.gold.ac.uk:/isms/group/muthic/darcs/amuse-viewpoints/  
PSGRAPH           http://www.cliki.net/psgraph

